    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hi @bobylito,\r\n\r\nI was more or less expecting to get a confirmation like this, I just hoped there was a way to achieve this.\r\nI got it working with changing the way the objects are structured in algolia.\r\n\r\nSomething like this:\r\n\"footballTeams\": [\r\n\t\"FCB:Barcelona\",\r\n\t\"RMA:Real Madrid\",\r\n\t\"JUV:Torino Juventus\"\r\n]\r\n\r\nBut to be honest I believe this approach is a bit rigid and I can't really think of a better solution right now. I just hoped there was something out of the box that would let me get data back but keeping data in algolia structured in a nice and correct way.\r\n\r\nThank you for your feedback though, really appreciate it",
